      "para_id": "Q001457.2",
      "line_range": "2",
      "translation": "(1) To Ningal , the beloved spouse of Suen , his lady , Ur-Namma , military governor of Urim , house-born slave of the E-kiš-nu-ĝal , his brother ... for the well-being of Utu-heĝal , the powerful man , king of Unug , king of four quarters ."
    }
